The article discusses the benefits of the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act (TCJA) in the United States. According to the Treasury's analysis, lower tax rates, higher standard deductions, and larger child tax credits have resulted in lower tax liability for most Americans. In 2018, a typical household earning $75,000 saw their taxes reduced by $2,244. The article also mentions that the American economy is stronger now, with increased business investment, consumer optimism, and job growth. The TCJA is credited with providing more jobs and higher wages for Americans.